@mistercrunch I'm running some tests, and I'm just wondering if by any chance the error object is not missing the `responseJSON` top object ?

I don't know if it is only for the tests, but this works :
```
// From /superset/assets/spec/javascripts/sqllab/actions_spec.js
it.only('return the correct error message on ajax error', () => {
      ajaxStub.yieldsTo('error', { responseJSON: {
        "query_id": 52,
        "status": "failed",
        "error": "relation \"javascrpt.pages\" does not exist\nLINE 12:    JOIN javascrpt.pages ON pages.anonymous_id = identifies.a...\n                 ^\n"
      }});
      makeRequest();
      expect(dispatch.callCount).to.equal(2);
      console.log("Query failed res: ", dispatch.getCall(1));
      expect(dispatch.getCall(1).args[0].type).to.equal(actions.QUERY_FAILED);
});
```
Error message:
```
args:
   [ { type: 'QUERY_FAILED',
       query: [Object],
       msg: 'relation "javascrpt.pages" does not exist\nLINE 12:    JOIN javascrpt.pages ON pages.anonymous_id = identifies.a...\n                 ^\n' } ],
```

